# Study Template

Use this template to document A/B tests, ablation studies, experiments, and other empirical investigations.

## File Organization Rules

**One file per study** - Keep all attempts, iterations, and learnings in a single file until the study is complete.

- If an attempt fails or is invalidated, add an "Attempt N (INVALIDATED)" section explaining what happened
- If you need to re-run, add "Attempt N+1" section below, don't create a new file
- Only create a new study file if the hypothesis or methodology fundamentally changes

**Why**: All context stays together, failed attempts become learning documentation, less file clutter.

**Example structure for multi-attempt study**:
```
## Attempt 1: {{ date | default('YYYY-MM-DD') }} (INVALIDATED)
### What Happened
[Results and why it was invalidated]

### Root Cause
[Bug or issue discovered]

---

## Attempt 2: {{ date | default('YYYY-MM-DD') }} (IN PROGRESS)
### Run Details
[Current attempt]
```

---

```yaml
---
# Required metadata
study_id: STU-YYYY-MM-DD-short-description
title: "Descriptive Title of the Study"
study_type: a_b_comparison  # a_b_comparison | ablation | hyperparameter | infrastructure | regression | exploratory
status: draft  # draft | in_progress | complete | abandoned
started: YYYY-MM-DD
completed: null  # YYYY-MM-DD when complete

# Categorization
tags: []  # e.g., [{{ config.study.example_tags | default('ml, optimization, feature-engineering') }}]
related_plans: []  # e.g., [102, 120] - plan numbers this relates to
related_studies: []  # e.g., [STU-2026-01-15-prior-study] - prior studies

# Variants being compared (minimum 2 for comparisons)
variants:
  - name: baseline
    description: "Description of baseline/control variant"
    config_ref: null  # optional: path to config file
{% if config.study.tracking_tool %}    {{ config.study.tracking_tool }}_run_ids: []  # optional: tracking run IDs for this variant
{% endif %}  - name: treatment
    description: "Description of treatment/experimental variant"
    config_ref: null
{% if config.study.tracking_tool %}    {{ config.study.tracking_tool }}_run_ids: []
{% endif %}
# Key metrics (flexible - add what's relevant)
# direction: higher_better | lower_better | target_value | neutral
metrics:
  - name: metric_name
    baseline: null
    treatment: null
    direction: higher_better
    unit: ""  # optional: e.g., "percent", "seconds", "score"

# Artifacts (links to evidence - all optional)
artifacts: []
# Example entries:
#   - type: state_file | log_file | config | notebook | experiment
#     path: relative/path/to/file
#     variant: baseline | treatment | both
#     description: "Optional description"

# Outcome (fill when complete)
outcome: null  # baseline_preferred | treatment_preferred | inconclusive | needs_followup
confidence: null  # low | medium | high
recommendation: null  # Brief recommendation statement
---
```

